NOTICE OF ASSOCIATION ASSESSMENT LIEN
PURSUANT TO A.R.S. $ 33-1256 OR $ 33-1807
Sundance Residential Homeowners Association, Inc, an Arizona Nonprofit Corporation ("Association"), hereby gives
notice that, pursuant to A.R.S. $ 33-1256 or $ 33-1807, the Association has a lien for assessments (and potentially other
amounts allowed by law) pursuant to the Association's Declaration of Covenants and Restrictions ("Declaration"), which
was recorded as Document Number 2002-0987138 on September 25, 2002 in the Maricopa County Recorder's Office
under Article IV, Section 4.07(d).
1. The legal description of the unit against which the lien exists (the "Unit") is Lot 99, of SUNDANCE PARCEL 37A,
according to the plat of record in the Office of the County Recorder of Maricopa County, Arizona, recorded
in Book 623 of Maps, Page 9 and Affidavits of Correction recorded as 2003-0935390 and as 2004-0451265,
both of Official Records.
a. Commonly known as;
23011 W Mohave Street
Buckeye, AZ 85326-6186
2. The owner of the Unit, according to the Association's records, is:
Emily J. Melchor
3. The amount of the lien, as of April 28, 2021, is: $653.24.
The amount of the lien may increase as set forth in the Declaration and A.R.S. $ 33-1256 or $ 33-1807
until it is satisfied in full.
IN WITNESS WHEREOF, I have hereunto set my hand this _5
Way of May
2021
By:
Jarred Greene, the Managing Agent of Sundance Residential
Homeowners Association, Inc
State of Arizona
County of Maricopa
5

day of

2021 by Jarred
Greene, the Managing Agent and Legal Document Preparer of AAM, LLC, an Arizona limited liability company, on
behalf of Sundance Residential Homeowners Association, Inc
Prepared by Jarred Greene, AZCLDP sesses
AAM, LLC AZCLOP #80511
Notary Public
Commission Expires:
3/29/24

JORDAN BACA
NOTARY PUBLIC - ARIZONA
MARICOPA COUNTY
COMMISSION # 579936
MY COMMISSION EXPIRES
MARCH 29, 2024
